Statement of Minister Sisulu on the withdrawal of the case against her advisor by the Hawks 3 June 2020 eval(ez_write_tag([[300,250],'politicsweb_co_za-box-3','ezslot_1',112,'0','0']));Minister Sisulu has noted the statement by the Directorate for Priority Crime investigation (The Hawks) on the outcomes of the investigation on her Advisor, Mphumzi Mdekazi. The Department has compiled affidavits of the various engagements between the department officials and the Directorate with regards to the matter. Such affidavits confirm communications from the Directorate which exonerated the Advisor of all allegations levelled against him and at this stage, that remains the view of the Department. The department considers the matter closed at this stage. Issued by Yonela Diko, Spokesperson, Department of Human Settlements, Water and Sanitation, 3 June 2020 eval(ez_write_tag([[580,400],'politicsweb_co_za-medrectangle-3','ezslot_2',113,'0','0']));